Debugging and Tracing</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cyrus-and/gdb-dashboard\">gdb-dashboard</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cyrus-and/gdb-dashboard\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">8.9k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":8900,\"repo\":\"cyrus-and/gdb-dashboard\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - GDB dashboard is a standalone .gdbinit file written using the Python API that enables a modular interface showing relevant information about the program being debugged.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-11T13:07:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>General cryptographic interest</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cryptojedi.org/papers/coolnacl-20120725.pdf\">The security impact of a new cryptographic library</a> - Introductory paper on NaCl, discussing important aspects of implementing cryptography and using it as a larger building block in security systems, by Daniel J. Bernstein, Tanja Lange, Peter Schwabe.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-11T13:05:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Secret key cryptography</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.iacr.org/archive/fse2015/85400168/85400168.pdf\">GCM Security Bounds Reconsidered</a> - An analysis and algorithm for nonce generation for AES GCM with higher counter-collision probability, by Yuichi Niwa, Keisuke Ohashi, Kazuhiko Minematsu, Tetsu Iwata.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-11T13:05:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Secret key cryptography</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://eprint.iacr.org/2019/806.pdf\">Proxy-Mediated Searchable Encryption in SQL Databases Using Blind Indexes</a> - An overview of existing searchable encryption schemes, and analysis of scheme built on AES-GCM, blind index and bloom filter by Eugene Pilyankevich, Dmytro Kornieiev, Artem Storozhuk.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-11T13:05:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Cryptanalysis</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://iacr.org/archive/eurocrypt2005/34940019/34940019.pdf\">How to Break MD5 and Other Hash Functions</a> - A 2005 paper about modular differential collision attack on MD5, MD4 and other hash functions, by Xiaoyun Wang and Hongbo Yu.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-11T13:05:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Cryptanalysis</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.iacr.org/archive/fse2012/75490447/75490447.pdf\">New attacks on Keccak-224 and Keccak-256</a> - A 2012 paper about using the combination of differential and algebraic techniques for collision attacks on SHA-3, by Itai Dinur, Orr Dunkelman, Adi Shamir.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-11T13:05:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Cryptanalysis</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.iacr.org/archive/fse2011/67330297/67330297.pdf\">A Single-Key Attack on the Full GOST Block Cipher</a> - An attack (\"Reflection-Meet-inthe-Middle Attack\") on GOST block cipher that allows to recover key with 2^225 computations and 2^32 known plaintexts, by Takanori Isobe.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-11T13:05:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Zero Knowledge Proofs</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007%2F978-3-319-96881-0_25\">Multi-Theorem Preprocessing NIZKs from Lattices</a> - Construction of non-interactive zero-knowledge (NIZK) proofs using lattice-based preprocessing models, by Sam Kim and David J. Wu.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-11T13:05:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Key Management</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://link.springer.com/content/pdf/10.1007/s00145-001-0009-4.pdf\">Selecting Cryptographic Key Sizes</a> - Classic paper from 1999 with guidelines for the determination of key sizes for symmetric cryptosystems, RSA, ECC, by Arjen K. Lenstra and Eric R. Verheul.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-11T13:05:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"awesome-selfhosted/awesome-selfhosted","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>Proxy</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://nginxproxymanager.com/\">Nginx Proxy Manager</a> - Nginx Proxy Manager is an easy way to accomplish reverse proxying hosts with SSL termination. (<a href=\"https://github.com/jc21/nginx-proxy-manager\">Source Code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jc21/nginx-proxy-manager\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">9.6k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":9606,\"repo\":\"jc21/nginx-proxy-manager\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->) <code>MIT</code> <code>Nodejs/Docker</code></li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-11T11:33:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"fkromer/awesome-ros2","categoryHTML":"<h2>Operating systems</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a hre